11.Name: open_wound_age_arterial
11.SqlCommand:
--Gets all CURRENT open wounds 
WITH OpenWounds AS (
    SELECT 
        w.id AS woundId,
        wst.startDateDimDateFk AS startDateDimDateFk,
        d.date AS startDate
    FROM rpt.Wound AS w
    INNER JOIN rpt.WoundState AS wst ON w.id = wst.woundFk
    INNER JOIN rpt.WoundStateType AS wstt ON wst.woundStateTypeFk = wstt.id
    INNER JOIN rpt.DimDate AS d ON wst.startDateDimDateFk = d.id
    WHERE wst.isCurrentState = 1
      AND wstt.name = 'open'
),

--Gets the woundFk's with a primary etiology of arterial ulcer at any given time
MostRecentEtiologies AS (
    SELECT 
        n.woundFk AS woundId,
        n.value AS primaryEtiology,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY n.woundFk ORDER BY n.dimDateFk DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM rpt.Note AS n
    INNER JOIN rpt.AttributeType AS atr ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
      AND n.value = 'Arterial Ulcer'
),

--Gets the woundFk's with most recent primary etiology as arterial ulcer
PrimaryEtiology AS (
    SELECT
        mre.woundId,
        mre.primaryEtiology AS primaryEtiology
    FROM MostRecentEtiologies AS mre
    WHERE mre.RowNum = 1
),

--Gets the difference between the startdate of the 'open' wound state and the current date as months open for all wounds that have a current state of open
WoundDurations AS (
    SELECT 
        ow.woundId,
        ow.startDate,
        DATEDIFF(MONTH, ow.startDate, GETDATE()) AS monthsOpen
    FROM OpenWounds AS ow
)

SELECT 
    wd.woundId,
    wd.startDate,
    wd.monthsOpen,
    CASE
        WHEN wd.monthsOpen BETWEEN 0 AND 3 THEN '0-3 months'
        WHEN wd.monthsOpen BETWEEN 4 AND 6 THEN '3-6 months'
        WHEN wd.monthsOpen BETWEEN 7 AND 9 THEN '6-9 months'
        WHEN wd.monthsOpen BETWEEN 10 AND 12 THEN '9-12 months'
        ELSE 'Over a year'
    END AS timeBracket,
    pe.primaryEtiology
FROM WoundDurations AS wd
INNER JOIN PrimaryEtiology AS pe 
    ON wd.woundId = pe.woundId
ORDER BY timeBracket, wd.woundId;

12.Name: braden_scale_healing
12.SqlCommand:
WITH BradenPatients AS (
    SELECT 
        n.patientFk AS patientId, 
        n.value AS bradenScaleRisk, 
        n.dimdateFk
    FROM 
        rpt.Note AS n
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AttributeType AS atr 
        ON atr.id = n.attributeTypeFk
    WHERE 
        atr.name = 'Braden Scale Risk'
),
MostRecentEtiologies AS (
    SELECT 
        n.woundFk AS woundId,
        n.patientFk AS patientId,
        n.value AS primaryEtiology,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY n.woundFk ORDER BY n.dimDateFk DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Note AS n
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AttributeType AS atr 
        ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE 
        atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
    AND n.value LIKE '%Pressure Ulcer%'
),
BradenScaleClosestToBaseline AS (
    SELECT
        bp.patientId,
        bp.bradenScaleRisk,
        bp.dimdateFk AS bradenDimDateFk,
        w.id AS woundId,
        w.BaselineDate AS woundBaselineDate,
        d.Date AS bradenDate,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY w.id 
            ORDER BY 
                CASE 
                    WHEN d.Date <= w.BaselineDate THEN 0 ELSE 1 
                END, 
                ABS(DATEDIFF(DAY, d.Date, w.BaselineDate)) 
        ) AS RowNum
    FROM
        rpt.Wound AS w
    INNER JOIN  
        BradenPatients AS bp
        ON w.patientFk = bp.patientId
    INNER JOIN  
        rpt.DimDate AS d
        ON bp.dimdateFk = d.id
),
HealedWounds AS (
    SELECT 
        ws.woundFk AS woundId,
        ws.startDate AS healedDate,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY ws.woundFk ORDER BY ws.startDate ASC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.WoundState AS ws
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.WoundStateType AS wstt 
        ON ws.woundStateTypeFk = wstt.id
    WHERE 
        wstt.name = 'Resurfaced/Resolved'
)
SELECT 
    bc.patientId,
    bc.woundId,
    mre.primaryEtiology,
    bc.bradenScaleRisk,
    bc.woundBaselineDate AS initialWoundDate,
    bc.bradenDate AS bradenDateClosestToBaseline,
    hw.healedDate,
    DATEDIFF(DAY, bc.woundBaselineDate, hw.healedDate) / 30 AS healingTimeMonths,
    CASE 
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, bc.woundBaselineDate, hw.healedDate) / 30 <= 3 THEN '0-3 months'
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, bc.woundBaselineDate, hw.healedDate) / 30 <= 6 THEN '3-6 months'
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, bc.woundBaselineDate, hw.healedDate) / 30 <= 9 THEN '6-9 months'
        WHEN DATEDIFF(DAY, bc.woundBaselineDate, hw.healedDate) / 30 <= 12 THEN '9-12 months'
        ELSE 'after 12'
    END AS healingTimeBracket
FROM 
    MostRecentEtiologies AS mre
INNER JOIN  
    BradenScaleClosestToBaseline AS bc
    ON mre.woundId = bc.woundId
    AND bc.RowNum = 1
INNER JOIN  
    HealedWounds AS hw
    ON bc.woundId = hw.woundId
    AND hw.RowNum = 1  -- Get the first time the wound was marked as healed
WHERE 
    mre.RowNum = 1
ORDER BY 
    bc.woundBaselineDate;

13.Name: braden_scale_individ
13.SqlCommand:
WITH BradenPatients AS (
    SELECT 
        n.patientFk AS patientId, 
        n.value AS bradenScaleRisk, 
        n.dimdateFk
    FROM 
        rpt.Note AS n
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AttributeType AS atr 
        ON atr.id = n.attributeTypeFk
    WHERE 
        atr.name = 'Braden Scale Risk'
),
MostRecentEtiologies AS (
    SELECT 
        n.woundFk AS woundId,
        n.patientFk AS patientId,
        n.value AS primaryEtiology,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY n.woundFk ORDER BY n.dimDateFk DESC) AS RowNum
    FROM 
        rpt.Note AS n
    INNER JOIN 
        rpt.AttributeType AS atr 
        ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE 
        atr.name = 'Primary Etiology'
),
BradenScaleClosestToBaseline AS (
    SELECT
        bp.patientId,
        bp.bradenScaleRisk,
        bp.dimdateFk AS bradenDimDateFk,
        w.id AS woundId,
        w.BaselineDate AS woundBaselineDate,
        d.Date AS bradenDate,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY w.id 
            ORDER BY 
                CASE 
                    WHEN d.Date <= w.BaselineDate THEN 0 ELSE 1 
                END, -- Prioritize Braden Scale before or on BaselineDate
                ABS(DATEDIFF(DAY, d.Date, w.BaselineDate)) -- Otherwise, find the closest
        ) AS RowNum
    FROM
        rpt.Wound AS w
    INNER JOIN  -- Changed from LEFT JOIN to INNER JOIN
        BradenPatients AS bp
        ON w.patientFk = bp.patientId
    INNER JOIN  -- Changed from LEFT JOIN to INNER JOIN
        rpt.DimDate AS d
        ON bp.dimdateFk = d.id
)
SELECT DISTINCT
    mre.patientId,
    mre.woundId,
    mre.primaryEtiology,
    bc.bradenScaleRisk,
    bc.woundBaselineDate AS initialWoundDate,
    bc.bradenDate AS bradenDateClosestToBaseline
FROM 
    MostRecentEtiologies AS mre
INNER JOIN  -- Changed from LEFT JOIN to INNER JOIN
    BradenScaleClosestToBaseline AS bc
    ON mre.woundId = bc.woundId
    AND bc.RowNum = 1 -- Ensure only the closest Braden Scale Risk is selected
WHERE 
    mre.RowNum = 1
ORDER BY 
    bc.woundBaselineDate;

        ON n.attributeTypeFk = atr.id
    WHERE

),
BradenScaleClosestToBaseline AS (
    SELECT
        bp.patientId,
        bp.bradenScaleRisk AS typeOfRisk,  
        bp.dimdateFk AS bradenDimDateFk,
        w.id AS woundId,
        w.BaselineDate AS woundBaselineDate,
        d.Date AS bradenDate,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY w.id 
            ORDER BY 
                CASE 
                    WHEN d.Date <= w.BaselineDate THEN 0 ELSE 1 
                END, 
                ABS(DATEDIFF(DAY, d.Date, w.BaselineDate))
        ) AS RowNum
    FROM
        rpt.Wound AS w
    INNER JOIN  
        BradenPatients AS bp
        ON w.patientFk = bp.patientId
    INNER JOIN  
        rpt.DimDate AS d
        ON bp.dimdateFk = d.id
)
SELECT 
    bc.typeOfRisk,  -- Braden Scale Risk type
    COUNT(*) AS totalWounds,
    COUNT(CASE WHEN mre.primaryEtiology = 'Pressure Ulcer (PU)/Pressure Injury (PI)' THEN 1 END) AS pressureUlcerCount,
    100.0 * COUNT(CASE WHEN mre.primaryEtiology = 'Pressure Ulcer (PU)/Pressure Injury (PI)' THEN 1 END) / COUNT(*) AS pressureUlcerPercentage,
    100 AS target,  -- Adding the target column with value 100 for each row
    CASE 
        WHEN bc.typeOfRisk = 'Very High Risk' THEN 5
        WHEN bc.typeOfRisk = 'High Risk' THEN 4
        WHEN bc.typeOfRisk = 'Moderate Risk' THEN 3
        WHEN bc.typeOfRisk = 'Mild Risk' THEN 2
        WHEN bc.typeOfRisk = 'No Risk' THEN 1
        ELSE 0  -- Default for any unexpected values
    END AS ranking
FROM 
    MostRecentEtiologies AS mre
INNER JOIN  
    BradenScaleClosestToBaseline AS bc
    ON mre.woundId = bc.woundId
    AND bc.RowNum = 1

    mre.RowNum = 1

    bc.typeOfRisk
